1,south,"**Analyzing the Sokoban Puzzle**

Okay, so I'm in a Sokoban-style game within MiniHack. My goal is to get these boulders (`\``) onto the fountains (`{`). I'm currently at position (40, 15), which I can see by checking where the `@` symbol is located. There are two boulders right next to me to the east, at (41, 15) and (42, 15). My initial thought was to simply push the first boulder east, expecting it to clear a path. However, after carefully considering the map and the layout of the adjacent spaces, I quickly realized that's not going to work, as the space directly east is also occupied by a boulder.

I need to confirm if I can move east at all. Re-examining the immediate surrounding area, specifically `#####<@``#`, I've confirmed that the boulders at (41,15) and (42,15) are, in fact, there. Pushing a boulder, as I recall, requires free space behind it. It looks like going around these boulders might be an option, but there's a wall `#` surrounding the area.

I checked my immediate surroundings to confirm the positions of the boulders:
```
8:  `######..{#`
9:  `#######`.#`
10: `#######.{#`
11: `#######.`#`
12: `#######{.#`
13: `#######..#`
14: `#####<@``#`
```
I can confirm that (39) is `<` (stairs), (40) is `@`, and (41) and (42) are the boulders. (43) is a wall.

I am now looking at the layout and seeing that I can't push east, given the initial state. The wall to the north is also blocking, so there is no movement to the North.
Re-examining the area more closely, specifically looking at all the numbers again and confirming that I am at (40, 15).
```
34-43: `##########`
34-43: `######..{#` -> 34:`, 39:#, 40:., 41:., 42:{, 43:#
34-43: `#######`.#` -> 34:#, ..., 40:#, 41:`, 42:., 43:#
34-43: `#######.{#` -> 40:#, 41:., 42:{, 43:#
34-43: `#######.`#` -> 40:#, 41:., 42:`, 43:#
34-43: `#######{.#` -> 40:#, 41:{, 42:., 43:#
34-43: `#######..#` -> 40:#, 41:., 42:., 43:#
34-43: `#####<@``#` -> 34:#.. 38:#, 39:<, 40:@, 41:`, 42:`, 43:#
```

I'm now thinking I can go south, as the row below `@` has `...` which is empty spaces. Therefore, I can go south and move the boulder from the west to the fountain on the east. Now, I'll go south and then east.","message:


