99,north,"**Analyzing the Boxoban Puzzle**

Okay, here's the deal. I'm in a Boxoban-like situation. I'm at coordinate (42, 13) and there are boulders (`) and fountains ({) on the map. The goal, as always, is to push the boulders onto the fountains.  I've got the map layout in front of me:

```
                                  ##########                                    
                                  ######..`#                                    
                                  #######``#                                    
                                  #######`{#                                    
                                  #######..#                                    
                                  #######{@#                                    
                                  #######..#                                    
                                  #####<{..#                                    
                                  ######...#                                    
                                  ##########                                    
```

So far, I've got my bearings. I'm located on the map at the `@` symbol at 42,13. I've been tracing the coordinates, and double-checking that I have the map layout correct. The fountains are at 42,11, 41,13, and 40,15. There are boulders at (42,9), (41,10), (42,10), and (41,11).

The problem is immediately obvious. The boulders around me at (41,10), (41,11), (42,9) and (42,10) are creating a bottleneck. I know that if I move north, there is a fountain at 42,11. The boulder at 42,10 is in the way. I need to get there and push that boulder south to cover the fountain.

The crucial issue is how to get the boulders to the right spots. The layout is tricky. The boulder at 42,10, to cover the fountain at 42,11. This means I would have to be at 42,9 to push south. But 42,9 is a boulder. I'm blocked. I'm going to have to get creative. I checked, and the agent has been at the position where the boulder and fountain meet.

I've been analyzing all the movement possibilities. I've looked at the history of previous movements. I've mapped the area. I thought that maybe, there was an alternate route, but there is not one. I've found that the boulders cannot be pushed from east-to-west, west-to-east, south-to-north, or north-to-south. I've checked every boulder, but it is impossible to push them in any direction. I checked the legend. I have looked at all the possibilities, and I seem to be missing something.

But there is a critical point! The agent has never tried to push the boulder located at (41,11) North. If the agent moves north, at the coordinate (42,12), moves west to (41,12) and then north again, what happens?  This might be the key to it all. I can't be sure, but it is the ONLY possible move that could solve the level. I've tried everything else, so let's try pushing the boulder north!","message:
